        <abstract> 
<p>Glad THH has taken up aphid question versus Owen ["On the agamic reproduction and morphology of <hi rend="italic">Aphis</hi>", <hi rend="italic">Trans. Linn. Soc. Lond.</hi> 22 (1858): 193–236].</p> 
            <p>Fertilisation and inheritance discussed. Speculates that fertilisation may be a mixture rather than a fusion. Can understand in no other way why crossed forms tend to go back to ancestral forms.</p>
        </abstract>
